# Page Object Layer Rules — "Find and Do"

You are editing a **Page Object** file. Pages are "dumb" — they contain ONLY
locator definitions and simple getter methods. ALL assertions live in Steps.

## Pattern to Follow

```javascript
const { BasePage } = require('../base.page');  // adjust depth as needed

class FeaturePage extends BasePage {
  constructor(page) {
    super(page);
    this.elementName = page.locator("selector");
    this.rowByName = (name) => page.locator(`tr:has-text("${name}")`);
  }

  async getFieldValue() {
    return await this.fieldLocator.textContent();
  }
}

module.exports = { FeaturePage };
```

## BasePage Provides These Methods (use freely)
- `this.waitForPageReady()` — DOM ready + network idle
- `this.waitForNetworkIdle(timeout)` — network idle only
- `this.smartWait({ timeout, additionalSelectors, waitForNetwork })` — wait for all loading spinners/skeletons to disappear
- `this.waitForStable(locator, stabilityMs, timeout)` — wait for element content to stop changing

## FORBIDDEN in Page Objects
- NO `expect()` calls — assertions belong EXCLUSIVELY in Steps
- NO complex business logic, NO click sequences, NO form fills
- NO importing `@playwright/test` for assertions
- NO verification methods (`verifyInputText`, `verifyErrorMessage`) — those are BaseSteps methods

## STRICT RULES
- Every class extends `BasePage`
- ALL locators defined in `constructor` as `this.name = page.locator(...)`
- Selector priority: `data-testid` > `aria-label/role` > `text` > semantic CSS
- NEVER use fragile CSS paths (`div > div > span:nth-child(3)`)
- NEVER use auto-generated class names (`css-1a2b3c`, `MuiButton-root`)
- ALWAYS export: `module.exports = { ClassName }`
- Modal pages go in `pages/{module}/modals/{feature}.modal.js`

## Locator Verification — MANDATORY Before Committing
- **NEVER guess** metric card titles, column header names, or element roles
- **ALWAYS verify** against the live DOM via browser inspection or test failure screenshots
- Common traps: column headers differ from what "sounds right"; view toggles may be `tab` not `button`
- When a text locator could match multiple elements (sidebar, modals, breadcrumbs), scope with `.first()`, `{ exact: true }`, or a parent container
